Boil a full kettle.

Meanwhile, grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{80%g} and @Red Leicester{60%g}. Drain and tear the @Mozzarella{1%ball}.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} on high heat. Stir in the @Macaroni{180%g} and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with @Olive Oil{1%tbsp} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

== Garlic Ciabatta ==

While the pasta cooks, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve the @Ciabatta{1} and lay onto one side of a large #baking tray{}, cut-side up.

Spread over the garlic and drizzle with the @Olive Oil{1%tbsp} for the garlic bread. Set aside for now.

== Cheese Sauce ==

Preheat your #grill{} to high.

Melt the @Butter{20%g} in a large saucepan on medium-high heat. Once hot, stir in the @Plain Flour{1.5%tbsp}. Cook until it forms a paste, ~{1-2%minutes} - you've made a roux!

Stir in the @Water{200%ml} a little at a time, followed by the @Vegetable Stock Paste{10%g}. Bring to the boil, stir continuously and simmer until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Mix in the @Creme Fraiche{150%g}, then remove from the heat.

== Mac and Cheese Assembly ==

Stir in the @Dijon Mustard{10%g}, cooked macaroni, Cheddar, Red Leicester and half the mozzarella until well combined and all the cheese has melted.

Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick. Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.

Transfer the mac and cheese to an appropriately sized #ovenproof dish{} and top with the remaining mozzarella.

Place the mac and cheese on the baking tray next to the garlic ciabatta and grill until both are golden, ~{5-6%minutes}.

== Balsamic Glazed Tomato Salad ==

Meanwhile, halve the @Baby Plum Tomatoes{125%g}.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine the @Balsamic Glaze{12%ml} and @Olive Oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then stir the tomatoes into the dressing.

Just before serving, add the @Baby Leaf Mix{50%g} to the tomatoes and toss to coat in the dressing.

Once the ciabatta is ready, cut it diagonally into triangles.

Share your ultimate mac and cheese between your plates.

Serve the garlic ciabatta and baby leaf salad alongside.

Enjoy!